metadata.name: Arachne
metadata.description:
Arachne (əˈræknɪ)  
n  
(Classical Myth & Legend) Greek myth a maiden changed into a spider for having presumptuously challenged Athena to a weaving contest

-

Unseen outtake from the "Eerie Polaroids" collection, minted as an open edition during spooky season. Taken with a Polaroid SX-70 and expired Impossible Project film.

Petrópolis, Brazil. 2019
